Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.59,0:00:06.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A mystery drama where Sakamoto Ryōma takes on a detective role in Nagasaki of the Bakumatsu period.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.90,0:00:11.40,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kōsaku Tatsumi (45)\NScriptwriter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.19,0:00:12.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}The scriptwriter writing the scenario,\NKōsaku Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, suddenly vanished,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.19,0:00:18.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and with the scenario not even half finished, the old man was asked to deduce the drama's culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.33,0:00:24.58,Signs,,0,0,0,,Serial Art Theft Case
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.29,0:00:27.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}When we took a look at Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s place, we found articles about art thieves pinned up in the closet, as if to hide them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.63,0:00:31.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It seems there's something else going on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.25,0:00:36.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, while still on the run, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} continued the scenario in an e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.01,0:00:45.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In it, a second murder occurs,{678 note: change 2nd "murder case" to "murder" in a similar line} and an unscheduled character, O-Tei of the Miura family appears,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.50,0:00:48.72,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and Ran ended up being dragged in to play O-Tei.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.61,0:00:53.03,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And because of that, I ended up like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.63,0:01:00.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Also, O-Tei has many curious lines, and for just those lines, a different font is used in the script.{script, screenplay? scenario's a bit of a wasei here, não? -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.83,0:01:04.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could these lines be a message from Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.13,0:01:08.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, an incident occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.20,0:01:11.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Prop Master, Sakota{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, was attacked by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.19,0:01:15.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.35,0:01:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.27,0:01:18.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran's the culprit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.18,0:01:23.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Vivid summer memories surpass their season to solve mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.93,0:01:26.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Can the Bakumatsu Drama be finished?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.18,0:01:28.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The suspicious staff hide secrets upon secrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.22,0:01:29.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.95,0:01:31.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.98,0:01:34.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.58,0:03:28.29,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kazuomi Sakota (35)\NProp Master
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.91,0:03:28.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}The wounds on Sakota{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s face were found to be from being punched by bare hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.29,0:03:33.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}so the Nagasaki Police are questioning Ran, a black belt in karate, as a suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.05,0:03:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.65,0:03:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was learning my lines alone then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:41.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can anyone verify that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.64,0:03:43.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't really know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.94,0:03:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! Something yellow went past me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.99,0:03:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.09,0:03:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No good, I can't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.58,0:04:00.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It was around here that Ran was learning her lines...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.61,0:04:05.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The only yellow things here are the flowers...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.92,0:04:07.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So it {\i1}was{\i0} a witness!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.54,0:04:13.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've no choice but to look for someone who saw Ran there when it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.86,0:04:15.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.83,0:04:19.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Puccini, the composer of the opera "Madame Butterfly".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.83,0:04:19.97,Signs,,0,0,0,,chōchō
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.05,0:04:19.97,Signs,,0,0,0,,Puccini Statue
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.89,0:04:26.60,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tamaki Miura Statue
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.59,0:04:26.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}And the opera singer who played the heroine Madame Butterfly, Tamaki Miura...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.60,0:04:28.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Miura?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.06,0:04:31.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Is there some connection to Ran's role, O-Tei of the Miura family?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.07,0:04:34.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sakota{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was an opera lover too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.57,0:04:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like Tamaki Miura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Teiko Kiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is famous for playing Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.09,0:04:44.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tamaki Miura and Teiko Kiwa...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.38,0:04:46.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}O-Tei of the Miura family!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.08,0:04:50.79,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shōkichi Shimizu (68)\NNagasaki Saruku Guide
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.30,0:04:50.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, let's move on to the next exhibit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.79,0:04:52.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yellow?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.59,0:04:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.13,0:04:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you seen this girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.92,0:05:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I remember her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.11,0:05:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw her engrossed reading something on a bench.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.85,0:05:10.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Thanks to the testimony of the guide, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, the suspicion on Ran was lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.26,0:05:16.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But then why had Sakota{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} pointed at Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.69,0:05:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, here I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.49,0:05:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just heard from the detectives that a man who looks like Tatsumi was seen in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.69,0:05:27.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.00,0:05:34.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Apparently after hearing screams from the parking lot, he ran off...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.25,0:05:34.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Taizō Ōki (52)\NDrama Production Company Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.04,0:05:35.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.34,0:05:38.51,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Futaba Nanao (23)\NAs Karasuma Ine
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.34,0:05:38.51,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ryūhei Kishimura (30)\NAssistant Director
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.57,0:05:37.35,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} wouldn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:38.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's gotta be a lie!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.51,0:05:40.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know something we don't?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.88,0:05:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.90,0:05:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean that, well, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} writes such brilliant scripts that I'm sure he wouldn't do something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.35,0:05:54.02,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Keisuke Sakakibara (45)\NTV Drama Director
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.35,0:05:54.02,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Akikazu Nakane (48)\NCameraman
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.02,0:05:52.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Let's leave the case to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.11,0:05:56.67,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the culprit in the drama...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.67,0:05:58.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.23,0:06:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I wonder why Sakota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was in this parking lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it too early for him to be going home?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.91,0:06:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The script had been continued, so you had to keep filming, so it's like he tried to sneak off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.06,0:06:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sneak off...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.67,0:06:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.34,0:06:23.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sakota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} read through the script, and realising he was in danger, he tried to run off!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.34,0:06:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Tatsumi predicted that Sakota would be attacked,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.12,0:06:29.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and left him a message in the script!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.98,0:06:34.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's likely contained in the dying message, "nine"!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.85,0:06:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what does the nine mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.70,0:06:40.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's pointing at you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.93,0:06:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Futaba Nanao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.07,0:06:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.91,0:06:47.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.58,0:06:49.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Simple addition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.58,0:06:53.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you add the the two of Futa{\c}ba and the seven of Nana{\c}o, you get nine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.33,0:06:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, it was a message saying that Futaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was targeting him, so he should be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.80,0:07:00.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.69,0:07:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why did you volunteer to be our guide?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.93,0:07:10.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it not to find Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} quickly so you could silence him just like Sakota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.62,0:07:11.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.89,0:07:15.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just worried about Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.32,0:07:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This seems like a bit of a stretch,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.48,0:07:20.57,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Benichiyo Yamashita (42)\NAs Tsuru
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,2 + 7 = 9...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.91,0:07:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The day's already over, so I'll be leaving for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.86,0:07:25.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, not yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.91,0:07:29.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh well. Let's stop filming for today then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.40,0:07:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hm? What's wrong, Ōki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.10,0:07:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Bara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, I just remembered,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.49,0:07:39.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,in her prime, O-Chiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was quite a famous actress for action stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.68,0:07:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.84,0:07:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, she did some Chinese martial arts.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.37,0:07:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though even Chō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} played a boxer once...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.39,0:07:52.35,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Chōjirō Sazanami (45)\NAs Soneya Chūbee
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.39,0:07:52.35,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kyōnosuke Sasahara (33)\NAs Sakamoto Ryōma
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.09,0:07:52.35,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Gimme a break, that was over twenty years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.75,0:07:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a mess...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.59,0:07:58.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More suspects keep popping up, and they're all actors...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.79,0:08:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, last night Andrew{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} may've been upset
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.73,0:08:08.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since Glover and Tsuru being married\Nwasn't historically accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.22,0:08:09.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was he?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.20,0:08:11.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.26,0:08:14.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsumi's the one who suggested that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.33,0:08:16.50,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Andrew Hatta (50)\NAs Glover
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.64,0:08:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.50,0:08:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, though it's unusual for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.30,0:08:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.22,0:08:29.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just about to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.14,0:08:29.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.72,0:08:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... But do something about it, I'm begging you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.90,0:08:44.69,Signs,,0,0,0,,Nagasaki Ropeway
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.69,0:08:45.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's wonderful...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.29,0:08:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Should we take a look?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.78,0:08:52.20,Signs,,0,0,0,,Mt. Inasa Viewing Platform
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.25,0:09:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was attacked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.58,0:09:04.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police just told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.65,0:09:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was at the Mt. Inasa Viewing Platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.17,0:09:09.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was he doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.21,0:09:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd take a look at the world-\Nrenowned night view of Nagasaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.14,0:09:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then I was suddenly attacked by someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.77,0:09:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I probably tore that off them in the struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.40,0:09:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems Tatsumi's fingerprints were on that strap.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.13,0:09:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What sort of strap was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.87,0:09:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was shaped like a silver heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.66,0:09:32.53,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A silver heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.53,0:09:33.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.08,0:09:37.50,Signs,,0,0,0,,Teramachi Street
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.59,0:09:43.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.42,0:09:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't look at the cameras, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.77,0:09:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.96,0:09:49.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why me too...?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.46,0:09:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.79,0:09:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told you, I know that already!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.64,0:09:59.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's always doing that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.98,0:10:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ready! Action!{Actually says "start", but mb "Aaaand... action" ? -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.58,0:10:07.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.32,0:10:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, the stroke order's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.02,0:10:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll rewind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.32,0:10:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not the first stroke, the sweeping stroke is!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.12,0:10:18.62,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That one was the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.54,0:10:25.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, as for that, see, a picture was attached to the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.11,0:10:28.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said to make it just like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.42,0:10:29.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Like I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.09,0:10:32.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Ask O-Tei of the Miura family"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.59,0:10:37.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Numbers are important. Numbers will solve everything"...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.59,0:10:42.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tamaki Miura and Teiko Kiwa, who played Madame Butterfly...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.92,0:10:44.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nine written in the wrong order...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.42,0:10:47.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Madame Butterfly{chouchou}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.45,0:10:48.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Chōchō{chouchou}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.12,0:10:50.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it! I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.05,0:10:53.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The meaning of the dying message is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.75,0:10:58.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"A demon lives here in Nakashima River."...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.50,0:11:02.69,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Its weak point is the second tooth from the left in its lower jaw."...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.69,0:11:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! Sorr—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.86,0:11:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, do that thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.06,0:11:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With your glasses!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.75,0:11:11.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? This?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.15,0:11:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.55,0:11:15.05,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.84,0:11:25.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.00,0:11:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A letter arrived from Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.20,0:11:43.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says he'll give us the rest of the script if we go to O-Shirasu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.38,0:11:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Shirasu?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.93,0:11:54.93,Signs,,0,0,0,,Nagasaki Museum of History and Culture
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.84,0:11:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you really get a letter from Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.93,0:12:00.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, saying he'd give us the rest of the script here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.77,0:12:04.94,Signs,,0,0,0,,O-Shirasu Theatre
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.99,0:12:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.26,0:12:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A theatre where plays are performed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.72,0:12:11.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are your wounds okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.11,0:12:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're not too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.86,0:12:17.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsumi's not here yet?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.26,0:12:20.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So all the actors are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.15,0:12:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} comes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.44,0:12:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I, Kogorō Mouri, will reveal the culprit to the real life case of who attacked Sakota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.23,0:12:34.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying it wasn't Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.65,0:12:37.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Tatsumi's fingerprints were on that strap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.77,0:12:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That strap was a trap set by the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.39,0:12:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The true culprit... is you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.28,0:12:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kyōnosuke Sasahara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.07,0:12:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Among the staff and cast, many people have numbers in their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.93,0:12:56.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you do too, Sasahara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.99,0:12:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where in my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:03.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}16
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:03.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}10
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}kyō{\i0} in Kyōnosuke Sasahara is a numerical unit if read as {\i1}kei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.46,0:13:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.28,0:13:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dying message in the script was also a number!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.51,0:13:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what about it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.57,0:13:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well... I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.50,0:13:19.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you always been making phone calls to someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.21,0:13:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And having arguments with them!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:24.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.15,0:13:29.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it not Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nthat you were arguing with?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.05,0:13:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.48,0:13:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll tell you the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was arguing with my agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.92,0:13:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have... a wife and child...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.67,0:13:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this is the first I've heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.55,0:13:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though you're a regular in\Nmost-wanted boyfriend rankings?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.47,0:14:03.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A weekly magazine found out, and I was being advertised as single, so I told my agency to stop them...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.68,0:14:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.70,0:14:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, so that's what was going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.71,0:14:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Benichiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.25,0:14:16.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you go out the night Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was attacked?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.24,0:14:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Now {\i1}I'm{\i0} your suspect?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.08,0:14:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.57,0:14:22.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Do I really have to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.47,0:14:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Chiyo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, don't tell me...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.60,0:14:26.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you go eat Turkish rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:33.68,Signs,,0,0,0,,Nagasaki\NSpecialty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:33.68,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Turkish Rice
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.40,0:14:33.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.84,0:14:37.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm supposed to be on a diet for my next job.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.48,0:14:42.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I couldn't resist the Nagasaki specialty, Turkish rice!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.60,0:14:44.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Then the culprit—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.98,0:14:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Spinning around again...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.26,0:14:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologise for that. Now for the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.03,0:14:56.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! This is the famous Sleeping Kogorō!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.70,0:14:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bring the camera!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.21,0:14:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.50,0:15:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I{\i0} wrote the letter that arrived from Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.00,0:15:05.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.86,0:15:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I could formally reveal the person who attacked Sakota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} {\i0}and Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.15,0:15:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit was...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.55,0:15:14.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...you, Ran!{lol, different wording to the NEP}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.84,0:15:15.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.34,0:15:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.20,0:15:19.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was her...?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.35,0:15:21.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on a sec, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.37,0:15:23.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calm down and listen, Ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.18,0:15:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the script, what was the dying message at the second murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.91,0:15:28.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.86,0:15:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the kanji numeral nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.09,0:15:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.52,0:15:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the stroke order was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.20,0:15:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see by looking at the marks left in the dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.65,0:15:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, the dying message was not the number nine,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.02,0:15:43.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the hiragana {\i1}te{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Te?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.16,0:15:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Ran, it was pointing to your role, O-Tei of the Miura family.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.09,0:15:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's for the case in the drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.18,0:16:01.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, I thought that Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s script was intended to reveal something about a real case at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.30,0:16:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A real case?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.46,0:16:05.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look closely at the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.39,0:16:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The font is different on specific lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.34,0:16:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they're a message from Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.40,0:16:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, O-Tei's lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.50,0:16:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Numbers are important. Numbers will solve everything.{Pasted from above}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.65,0:16:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this line and the dying message, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.40,0:16:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was pointing to a letter connected with\Nthe number in a certain person's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.00,0:16:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.25,0:16:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chōjirō Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s {\i1}chō{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:41.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.34,0:16:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.85,0:16:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.53,0:16:47.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What're you saying, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.06,0:16:50.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm saying that the culprit in a series of cases is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.94,0:16:53.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wait{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.10,0:16:56.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For {\i1}chō{\i0}, shouldn't {\i1}chi{\i0} have been left instead of {\i1}te{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.15,0:16:57.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.19,0:17:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the old Japanese kana orthography,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.30,0:17:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{sign: Butterfly(chouchou(tefutefu))}\N'butterfly{chouchou}' was written {\i1}tefutefu{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:05.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where'd you get butterfly{chouchou} from all of a sudden!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.18,0:17:11.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s messages were closely connected with Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.65,0:17:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For further information, ask the daughter of the Miura shipping agency, O-Tei.{paste from 678}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.74,0:17:20.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This font was different for this line too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.50,0:17:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If "O-Tei of the Miura family"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.51,0:17:27.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,was named after the opera singers who played Madame Butterfly,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.31,0:17:33.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Tamaki Miura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Teiko Kiwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, then O-Tei is connected with Madame Butterfly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.08,0:17:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically, the dying message was the {\i1}te{\i0} of {\i1}tefutefu{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.23,0:17:38.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.98,0:17:40.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You're twisting facts!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.78,0:17:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One theory is that the model for Madame Butterfly was Glover's wife, Tsuru.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.35,0:17:53.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} even went against historical fact to include Tsuru in the drama was to prepare for this message.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.46,0:18:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Tatsumi meant to reveal Chō{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in his script from the very start?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.79,0:18:01.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.76,0:18:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the case hadn't happened until after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.40,0:18:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was revealing was another case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.18,0:18:10.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another case?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.31,0:18:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one who realised it was the opera lover, Sakota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.48,0:18:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when trying to escape by himself before I could solve the mystery, he was attacked by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason Sakota{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} pointed at Ran was because O-Tei was a character created to reveal Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.98,0:18:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.25,0:18:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then they're both accomplices in something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:34.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.27,0:18:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.61,0:18:39.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These were at Tatsumi's place...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.50,0:18:42.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me it's about this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.26,0:18:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gimme a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.77,0:18:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was attacked by Tatsumi after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.55,0:18:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was your own performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.01,0:18:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to incriminate Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.31,0:18:54.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.60,0:18:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's awful...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.31,0:18:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's bull!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.53,0:18:59.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.91,0:19:02.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me show you some conclusive proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.45,0:19:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember O-Tei's line, "A demon lives here in Nakashima River"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.76,0:19:09.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.40,0:19:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.81,0:19:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Demon? Isn't that Spectacles Bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.87,0:19:19.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you know, if you do this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:25.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? It looks like a demon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.89,0:19:27.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.15,0:19:34.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the demon's weak point being the second tooth from the left in its lower jaw meant this stepping stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.93,0:19:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Kogorō told me to check it, and last night I found this there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.97,0:19:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Micro SD card.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.90,0:19:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister, will you show us what's on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.64,0:19:45.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.30,0:19:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're not gonna use these props anymore, so let's put them in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.42,0:19:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plenty more easy money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.53,0:19:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.54,0:20:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you saw, the stolen works of art were hidden in the props used for filming,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.50,0:20:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and when they arrived on location, were secretly sold to collectors or rich people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.57,0:20:04.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This video proves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.15,0:20:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} tried to reveal this in the script for the drama, but hid as he felt he was in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.44,0:20:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he found out Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had arrived, and tried to sneak clues in when continuing the script, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.20,0:20:25.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sleeping Kogorō, solve this puzzle!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.88,0:20:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's just like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.40,0:20:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So where is Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.21,0:20:34.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} knows where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.09,0:20:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I don't know...{know -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.38,0:20:38.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why should I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.85,0:20:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.30,0:20:43.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's {\i1}Sensei{\i0}... Where is Kōsaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!{first use of first name}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.29,0:20:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't talk your way out of this, Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.39,0:20:55.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, {\i1}you're{\i0} the one who had the strap with Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.98,0:21:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Futaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, don't tell me you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.73,0:21:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and Tatsumi are...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.39,0:21:12.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The reason she offered to help me was because she wanted to save her beloved, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.97,0:21:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.12,0:21:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my agency bans relationships, so I had to keep it a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.82,0:21:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.35,0:21:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if he had this much evidence, why didn't Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} go to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.01,0:21:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he wanted him to give himself in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.84,0:21:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this drama with all his old friends in,\Nhe wanted to force Sazanami to repent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.84,0:21:42.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kōsaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.60,0:21:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Futaba!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.68,0:23:15.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In the ICU, Sakota{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} regained consciousness, and supported the case with his testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.34,0:23:20.55,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The art theft ring they were part of will likely be unmasked someday.{thief -> theft? -uso.}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.55,0:23:22.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The drama's filming resumed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.31,0:23:33.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Of course, as well as removing scenes including Sazanami{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, Ran and me, Tatsumi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} rapidly fixed up a new script.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.04,0:23:41.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard the agency's supported their relationship!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.14,0:23:44.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's good for them!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.75,0:23:46.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.16,0:23:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you write Nagasaki in rōmaji,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.85,0:23:51.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}ai
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.85,0:23:51.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it ends in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.17,0:23:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like for those two...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.40,0:24:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this the cactus we heard about?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.54,0:24:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister!{oji-sama!}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.88,0:24:07.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bro, then you really did...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.74,0:24:09.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No! I didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.38,0:24:11.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see. So that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.01,0:24:14.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then the killer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.22,0:24:18.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that alarm, I figured everything out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.30,0:24:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.43,0:24:25.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: Cactus Capriccio!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.44,0:24:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Heater!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.44,0:24:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a1}Dad's so cool when he's asleep!
